rComments: If you don't have a passion for history/classics, then this probably isn't the class for you. Lectures are really boring but powerpoint slides are detailed so that helps. Read the textbook and go to class! The midterm/exam have VERY specific questions related to class material, so pay attention! He's a nice prof, but it's not a bird course.

Nice guy; speaks in monotone. Gives no breaks, easy to fall asleep in lecture. Don't need to come to class if you look over his powerpoints and do all the readings. Exams are painfully specific for the amount of content we cover throughout the course.

Very boring teacher. He writes ALL of his notes on powerpoint and just reads off of them. There were at least 90+ slides. His midterm and exams were okay if you knew the content. All you  have to do in his class is to read the readings. He's a kind man, but so boring.
